text:
Try their char ziu wan tan noodle 5 dollar only.
Portion wise 5 mouth finished.
The taste wise OK nia.
Still not satisfy my appetite.
Overall just fine.
May be i will try their wok fried next time.
Nice Hong Kong style roasted pork and char siew. Non-aircon, so a bit on the warm side.
Roasted duck leg noodle $10. The skin cannot chew at all, too hard already
After the chef change the food quality became non existent. Price is way too expensive for the kind of quality.
Beside hong Kong style of duck, pork, etc, they also provide seafood serving and noodle ... many choices for your lunch as well as dinner
